 (2018) show reduced ex vivo production of 11KT in male Zebrafish, due to gemfibrozil exposure, is corrected by addition of 25-hydroxycholesterol. This means the decreased steroid synthesis is due to decreased cholesterol availability. Addition of human chorionic gonadotropin, which binds to the LHCG receptor to promote 11KT synthesis, does not correct the decrease in 11KT.", "timestamp": "Mon Jun 08 15:26:02 +0000 2026"}